TopicTitle: Any mods known for wiping every single ship on a save?

Articles.Content: I had a modded install. Had. Now even the Squad parts have vanished from the VAB. The GAMEDATA folder is still intact
Is it a career save? I think I've seen that sort of thing happen during testing when two parts have the same name in their cfg. It causes an error where everything after that part wont load.

Is it a career save? I think I've seen that sort of thing happen during testing when two parts have the same name in their cfg. It causes an error where everything after that part wont load.

It was in sandbox as well. I've singled out a few folders: CactEye, Hullcam and Bdanimsource

Presumably you have an install error, and something's breaking during load.

Upload your output log (NOT ksp.log) to dropbox or something.

Windows: KSP_win\KSP_Data\output_log.txt

Mac OSX: Open Console, on the left side of the window there is a menu that says 'files'. Scroll down the list and find the Unity drop down, under Unity there will be Player.log Aka Files>~/Library/Logs>Unity>Player.log

Linux: ~/.config/unity3d/Squad/Kerbal\ Space\ Program/Player.log
